<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

  <title>Rog-Time</title>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/style.css">
</head>

<body>

  <%- include('partials/nav.ejs') %>

  <main>

    <section class="hero" style="background-image: url('https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/original<%= heroBackdrop %>');">
      <div class="hero-content">

        <p class="hero-label">YOUR MOVIE ACTIVITY AWAITS</p>

        <h1>
          Your watchlist deserves better.
        </h1>

        <p class="hero-description">
          Discover movies, log what you watched, rate films, and publish
          reviews that may or may not get your movie privileges questioned.
        </p>

        <% if (user) { %>

          <p class="welcome-message">
            Welcome back,
            <strong><%= user.username %></strong>.
            Your cinematic judgment will now be evaluated.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-buttons">
            <a href="/movies" class="main-button">
              Enter the Movie Realm
            </a>

            <a href="/dashboard" class="secondary-button">
              View Your Records
            </a>
          </div>

        <% } else { %>

          <p class="visitor-message">
            Create an account before your watch history becomes completely
            unsalvageable.
          </p>

          <div class="hero-buttons">
            <a href="/auth/sign-up" class="main-button">
              Begin Your Development
            </a>

            <a href="/auth/sign-in" class="secondary-button">
              Return to the Arena
            </a>
          </div>

        <% } %>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="features">

      <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label">THE SYSTEM</p>
          <h2>Everything you need to defend your movie taste.</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-grid">

        <article class="feature-card">
          <p class="feature-number">01</p>

          <h3>Discover</h3>

          <p>
            Search for movies and find something worth two hours of your
            existence.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="feature-card">
          <p class="feature-number">02</p>

          <h3>Track</h3>

          <p>
            Log watched movies before your memory completely abandons you.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="feature-card">
          <p class="feature-number">03</p>

          <h3>Review</h3>

          <p>
            Rate movies and explain why everyone else misunderstood the
            director’s vision.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="feature-card">
          <p class="feature-number">04</p>

          <h3>Top Five</h3>

          <p>
            Select five movies to represent you. Choose carefully. This is
            permanent evidence of your judgment.
          </p>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>
<section class="popular-preview">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <div>
      <p class="section-label">CURRENTLY DOMINATING</p>
      <h2>Popular Movies</h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="movie-grid">
    <% popularMovies.forEach(function(movie) { %>
      <div class="movie-poster">
        <img src="https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w300<%= movie.poster_path %>" alt="<%= movie.title %>">
        <p><%= movie.title %></p>
      </div>
    <% }) %>
    <a href="/movies" class="text-link">
  View the full selection
</a>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="ltg-spotlight">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <div>
      <p class="section-label">CURRENTLY DOMINATING (FOR REAL THIS TIME)</p>
      <h2>Top Movie Right Now</h2>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="ltg-card">
    <img src="/images/images (6).jpg" alt="LowTierGod movie moment">

    <div class="ltg-text">
      <h3>The LowTierGod Cinematic Universe</h3>
      <p>
        Critics call it "unwatchable." Historians call it "a warning."
        We call it Movie of the Year. No script, no budget, no plan —
        just pure, unfiltered chaos energy carrying the entire runtime.
      </p>
      <p>
        Best Written Character 2026: a man whose entire arc is refusing
        to have one. No redemption, no character growth, just vibes and
        volume. Truly avant-garde storytelling.
      </p>
      <p>
        Rated 5 stars for realism. 0 stars for decision-making.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
    <section class="final-message">
      <p>
        Poor ratings are temporary. Your review history is forever.
      </p>
    </section>

  </main>

  <footer>
    <p>
      Rog-Time &copy; 2026 — Your cinematic records have been documented.
    </p>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>